---
import ContentLayout from '../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';

const toc = [
  { id: 'getting-started', text: 'Getting Started', level: 2 },
  { id: 'development-environment', text: 'Development Environment', level: 2 },
  { id: 'editor-setup', text: 'Editor Setup', level: 3 },
  { id: 'extensions', text: 'Recommended Extensions', level: 3 },
  { id: 'project-structure', text: 'Project Structure', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coding-standards', text: 'Coding Standards', level: 2 },
  { id: 'next-steps', text: 'Next Steps', level: 2 },
];
---

<ContentLayout
  title="New Developer Onboarding"
  description="Welcome to the team! This guide will help you get started with our development environment and processes."
  toc={toc}
>
  <section id="getting-started" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white">Getting Started</h2>
    <p class="mt-4">
      Welcome to our development team! This guide will walk you through everything you need to know
      to get started as a developer in our organization. We'll cover setting up your development
      environment, understanding our project structure, and following our coding standards.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="development-environment" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white">Development Environment</h2>
    <p class="mt-4">
      Our development environment is designed to be consistent across the team and easy to set up.
      Here's what you'll need to install:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-4 space-y-2">
      <li>Node.js (LTS version)</li>
      <li>Git</li>
      <li>Visual Studio Code</li>
      <li>Docker Desktop</li>
    </ul>

    <div id="editor-setup" class="mt-8">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Editor Setup</h3>
      <p class="mt-4">
        We recommend using Visual Studio Code as your primary code editor. It provides excellent
        support for our tech stack and can be configured with team-shared settings.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div id="extensions" class="mt-8">
      <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Recommended Extensions</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-4 space-y-2">
        <li>ESLint</li>
        <li>Prettier</li>
        <li>GitLens</li>
        <li>Tailwind CSS IntelliSense</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="project-structure" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white">Project Structure</h2>
    <p class="mt-4">
      Our projects follow a consistent structure to make it easy to navigate and maintain:
    </p>
    <pre class="mt-4 p-4 bg-slate-800 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto">
/src
  /components   # Reusable UI components
  /layouts      # Page layouts and templates
  /pages        # Route pages
  /utils        # Utility functions
  /styles       # Global styles
  /types        # TypeScript type definitions
/public         # Static assets
/tests          # Test files</pre>
  </section>

  <section id="coding-standards" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white">Coding Standards</h2>
    <p class="mt-4">
      We follow industry best practices and have established coding standards to maintain
      consistency across our codebase:
    </p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-4 space-y-2">
      <li>Use TypeScript for all new code</li>
      <li>Follow ESLint and Prettier configurations</li>
      <li>Write unit tests for all new features</li>
      <li>Use meaningful commit messages following conventional commits</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section id="next-steps" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white">Next Steps</h2>
    <p class="mt-4">
      Now that you're familiar with our basic setup, here are your next steps:
    </p>
    <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mt-4 space-y-2">
      <li>Set up your development environment</li>
      <li>Clone our starter project</li>
      <li>Read through our coding standards</li>
      <li>Complete the onboarding tasks in our project management tool</li>
    </ol>
  </section>
</ContentLayout>